ter slide by ProSlide. Opened in 2002.\n* El Tif\u00f3n \u2013 Two typhoon Water Slide by ProSlide. Opened in 2002.\n* El R\u00edo Loco \u2013 Lazy River. Opened in 2002.\n* El Torrente \u2013 A 4-passenger tube by ProSlide. Opened in 2002.\n* Barracudas \u2013 A pair of 2 Passenger tube sails through tunnels and spins at full speed by ProSlide. Opened in 2002.\n\n===Kids rides===\n* Zona Indoor with Junior Slides \u2013 Indoor play area including pool and slides by [[WhiteWater West]]. Opened in 2002.\n* La Laguna de Woody \u2013 [[Woody Woodpecker]]-themed play area by WhiteWater West. Opened in 2002.\n\n==Resort hotels==\nThe resort features six thematic hotels:\n\n* ''PortAventura Hotel PortAventura'': Mediterranean theme (4*).\n* ''PortAventura Hotel Caribe'': Caribbean theme (4*).\n* ''PortAventura Hotel El Paso'': Mexican theme (4*).\n* ''PortAventura Hotel Gold River'': Far West theme (4*).\n* ''PortAventura Hotel Colorado Creek'': Far West theme (4*).\n* ''PortAventura Hotel Mansi\u00f3n de Lucy'': Victorian-style Far West theme (5*).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.incentivetravel.co.uk/destination-reports/fam-trip-reports/29660-portaventura-a-world-class-and-versatile-events-option|title=PortAventura \u2013 a world class and versatile events option|date=2 November 2015|website=incentivetravel.co.uk|author=Michelle Chenery|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref>\n* ''Hotel Ferrari'': Ferrari theme (5*) ''(future)''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2014/mar/13/ferrari-land-theme-park-portaventura-barcelona|title=Ferrari theme park to open at PortAventura resort near Barcelona|date=13 March 2014|website=[[The Guardian]]|author=Ashifa Kassam|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Seasonal events==\n[[File:FiestAventura logo PA.JPG|thumb|FiestAventura]]\n{{tone|section|date=November 2018}}\nDuring seasonal events like summer nights, Halloween (September\u2013November) and Christmas (November\u2013January), PortAventura Park opens seasonal walkaround rides or shows, including the mazes: [REC], Horror in Penitence, La Selva del Miedo and the nighttime Halloween show Horror en el Lago.\n\n{{hidden|Some events|;Summer\n* Dance Revolution \u2013 At the Gran Teatro Imperial Theatre.\n* PortAventura Parade \u2013 A parade with music and choreography, leading up to the start of the FiestAventura show.\n* FiestAventura \u2013 The fireworks show including water effects and floats. That's clausure the day.\n\n;Halloween\n\n* Halloween Kingdom \u2013 At the Gran Teatro Imperial Theatre.\n* [REC] Experience \u2013 Passage of terror.\n* Horror in Penitence \u2013 Passage of terror.\n* La Selva del Miedo \u2013 Passage of terror.\n* Halloween Parade \u2013 A parade with music and choreography of the most terrorific monsters at the park, leading up to the start of the Horror en el Lago show.\n* Horror en el Lago \u2013 The fireworks show including water effects and floats. That's clausure the day.\n\n;Christmas\n\n* PortAventura Christmas World \u2013 At the Gran Teatro Imperial Theatre.\n* Cuento de Navidad \u2013 Magnificent artistic and acrobatic display with international ice-skaters\n* Christmas Family Festival \u2013 A family area only for Christmas.\n* Christmas Parade \u2013 A parade with music and choreography full of christmas lights an christmas carriages, leading up to the start of the La llegada de los Emisarios Reales.\n* La llegada de los Emisarios Reales \u2013 The Three Kings helpers arrive at the lake with a great multimedia firework show.}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Incidents at European amusement parks]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|PortAventura World}}\n* {{in lang|en}} [https://www.portaventuraworld.com/en \u2013 Official English site]\n\n{{PortAventura World}}\n{{Universal Parks & Resorts}}\n{{John Wardley}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Portaventura}}\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|PortAventura Park}}\n{{more citations needed|date=January 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2011}}\n{{Infobox amusement park\n| name = PortAventura World\n| logo = PortAdventura World Logo.svg\n| caption = \n| location = [[Salou]] and [[Vila-seca]]\n| location2 = [[Catalonia]]\n| location3 = [[Spain]]\n| coordinates = {{Coord|41.086839|1.157272|type:landmark_source:enwiki-googlemaplink|display=it}}\n| homepage = {{Official website|https://www.portaventuraworld.com/en}}\n| owner = InvestIndustrial and [[Kohlberg Kravis Roberts|KKR]]\n| general_manager = Sergio Feder\n| operator        = InvestIndustrial \n| opening_date = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2002|6|13}} (resort)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parquestematicos.org/noticias/2002/ver-noticia.asp?id=33|title=Universal Mediterr\u00e1nea destinado a ser el destino familiar m\u00e1s importante de Europa|publisher=parquestematicos.org|date=13 June 2002|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref><br />{{Start date and age|df=yes|1995|5|1}} (first park)\n| previous_names = <small>* Universal Mediterranea (2002-2004),<br />* PortAventura (2005-2012),<br />* PortAventura European Destination Resort (2013-2015)</small>\n| season = Spring through winter\n| visitors        = 4.9 million (2018)<ref name=\"report5\"/>\n| area            = 119 [[hectare|ha]] <ref name=\"report3\"/><br />294 acres\n| rides = 53\n| coasters = 9\n| water_rides = 5\n| slogan = Parks & Resort\n}}\n\n'''PortAventura World''' is an entertainment [[resort]] in [[Salou]] and [[Vila-seca]], [[Province of Tarragona|Tarragona]], on the [[Costa Daurada]] in [[Catalonia]], [[Spain]]. It was built around the [[PortAventura Park]] [[Amusement park|theme park]], which attracts around 3.5 million visitors per year, making it the most visited theme park in Spain and the sixth most visited theme park in Europe.<ref>{{cite journal| author = [[Themed Entertainment Association]]|author2=Economics Research Associates| title = Global attractions attendance report| publisher = AECOM| year = 2013 | url =http://www.teaconnect.org/images/files/TEA_28_915227_140617.pdf| format = PDF|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref> The resort includes a second theme park, Ferrari Land, since 2017 and also includes PortAventura Caribe Aquatic Park, five hotels, a convention centre and a [[RV park]]. It is the biggest resort in the south of Europe which attracts around 5 million visitors per year. It has [[Reus Airport]] within 15 minutes of it and [[Barcelona\u2013El Prat Airport|Barcelona Airport]] within an hour.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portaventuraworld.com/en/destination/planning/how-to-get-to-portaventura|title=How to get to PortAventura|publisher=portaventura.co.uk|accessdate=17 February 2015}}</ref> There is a train station for PortAventura which has connections to Barcelona, Salou and Tortosa.\n\n==History==\n\n'[[PortAventura Park|Port Aventura]]' opened in 1995 in Salou,<ref>{{cite web|title=Europe's Second Theme Park Planned in Spain|author= Richard Schweid|publisher=Associated Press|website=AP news Archive|url=https://apnews.com/2a431d8802d7d1567aabaf729b45e117|date=2 November 1992|accessdate=5 May 2017}}</ref> [[The Tussauds Group|Tussauds Group]] had a 40,01% in the park while [[La Caixa]] had 33,19%, [[Anheuser-Busch]] had 19,9% and FECSA had 6,7%.<ref>{{cite news |title=Naissance de Port Aventura, gigantesque parc de loisirs pr\u00e8s de Barcelone|url=https://www.liberation.fr/futurs/1995/04/24/naissance-de-port-aventura-gigantesque-parc-de-loisirs-pres-de-barcelone_129288|accessdate=28 October 2018|work=liberation.fr|date=24 April 1995}}.</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blooloop.com/features/ray-barratt/24440#.UmY5xFBeZ8E |title=Ray Barratt |publisher=blooloop |date=2013-08-30 |accessdate=2016-04-28 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109030855/http://www.blooloop.com/features/ray-barratt/24440#.UmY5xFBeZ8E |archivedate=9 November 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=La Generalitat tomar\u00e1 y el 10% del parque de Salou si Busch recupera la mayor\u00eda|url=https://elpais.com/diario/1993/01/29/economia/728262002_850215.html|accessdate=28 October 2018|author=Josep Maria Cortes, Manel Perez|work=elpais.com|date=29 January 1993}}.</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=The Global Theme Park Industry|author=Salvador Anton Clav\u00e9|date=16 April 2007|page=131|publisher=CABI|ISBN=978-1845932084}}</ref> In 1998 the majority of Tussauds Group'shares in the park were sold to [[Universal Parks & Resorts|Universal]] and the park was rebranded as 'Universal's Port Aventura', which made it the first Universal Studios Theme Park in Europe.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/pearson-raises-pounds-58m-on-sale-of-spanish-theme-park-stake-1166965.html|title=Pearson raises pounds 58m on sale of Spanish theme park stake|newspaper=independent.co.uk|date=23 June 1998|accessdate=28 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Pearson Completes Tussauds Group Disposal|url=https://www.pearson.com/corporate/news/media/news-announcements/1998/10/pearson-completes-tussauds-group-disposal.html|accessdate=18 October 2018|work=pearson.com|date=19 October 1998}}.</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Veremonte y La Caixa se al\u00edan en Barcelona World |url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/economia/20120907/54348156782/veremonte-la-caixa-barcelona-world.html |accessdate=26 July 2018 |work=La Vanguardia |date=9 July 2012}} [https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=es&tl=en&js=y&prev=_t&hl=en&ie=UTF-8&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lavanguardia.com%2Feconomia%2F20120907%2F54348156782%2Fveremonte-la-caixa-barcelona-world.html&edit-text= Translation: \"Veremonte and La Caixa team up in Barcelona World\"].</ref>\n\nIn 2002, a water park (''Costa Caribe'') and two hotels (''Hotel PortAventura'' and ''Hotel El Paso'') were constructed, and the resort was further rebranded as 'Universal Mediterranea'.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leisureopportunities.co.uk/news/Universal-Mediterranea-near-completion/1680|title=Universal Mediterranea near completion|date=26 February 2002|website=leisureopportunities.co.uk|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diaridetarragona.com/tarragona/Del-Dragon-Khan-al-mayor-polo-turistico-del-Mediterraneo-20170710-0077.html|title=Del Dragon Khan al mayor polo tur\u00edstico del Mediterr\u00e1neo|publisher=diaridetarragona.com|accessdate=10 July 2017}}</ref> In 2004, [[NBCUniversal]] (Universal Studios' parent) sold all interest in PortAventura.<ref>{{cite news |title=U sells Port Aventura stake|url=https://variety.com/2004/biz/news/u-sells-port-aventura-stake-1117906749/|accessdate=28 October 2018|work=variety.com|date=20 June 2004}}.</ref> It is owned and operated by [[La Caixa]] banking group's investment vehicle [[CaixaBank|Criteria]], but as of 2005 the Universal name has been dropped from the branding, and the resort was once again named 'PortAventura' (the space in the name is deliberately left out for trademark reasons). In 2009, the resort hosted 3,310,000 visitors.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blooloop.com/link/spain-port-aventura-registered-3310000-visitors-representing-a-decrease-of-8-over-the-previous-year/|title=Spain: Port Aventura, registered 3, 310, 000 visitors, representing a decrease of 8% over the previous year|date=26 February 2010|website=blooloop.com|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2013 KKR <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altassets.net/private-equity-news/by-news-type/deal-news/kkr-picks-up-49-9-stake-in-portaventura-from-investindustrial.html |title=KKR picks up 49.9% stake in PortAventura from Investindustrial &#124; AltAssets Private Equity News |publisher=Altassets.net |date=2013-12-06 |accessdate=2016-04-28}}</ref> picks up 49.9% stake in PortAventura from Investindustrial that still owns 50.1%. In 2016 the resort was renamed as 'PortAventura World Parks & Resort'.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inparkmagazine.com/port-aventura-world-rebranding/|title=PortAventura Rebrands with New Website in Anticipation of Ferrari Land|date=26 January 2016|website=inparkmagazine.com|author=Joe Kleiman|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref> The second theme park, Ferrari Land, was inaugurated on 7 April 2017.<ref name=\"FerrariLand\">{{cite news|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/ocio/20150507/54431093582/ferrari-land-portaventura-empleos.html|title=Ferrari Land estar\u00e1 separado de PortAventura y crear\u00e1 150 empleos|newspaper=[[La Vanguardia]]|date=7 May 2015|accessdate=2 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n<center>\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:right;\" border=\"4\" cellpadding=\"3\"\n|+ Annual visits<ref name=\"report\">{{cite web|url=http://www.investindustrial.com/dam/Investindustrial/Social-responsibility/Portoflio-Companies-CSR-Reports/PORTAVENTURA-CSR-Report-2016/PORTAVENTURA%20CSR%20Report%202016.PDF|title=Corporate responsibility report '16|date=2017|publisher=investindustrial.com|author=|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"report2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.investindustrial.com/dam/Investindustrial/Social-responsibility/Portoflio-Companies-CSR-Reports/PortAventura-2017-Corporate-Social-Responsibility-Report/PortAventura%202017%20Corporate%20Social%20Responsibility%20Report.pdf|title=Corporate responsibility report 2017|date=2018|publisher=investindustrial.com|author=|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"report3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fundacioportaventura.org/docs/documentacion/doc_20141125102547.pdf|title=Annual report Corporate responsibility 2012|date=2013|publisher=fundacioportaventura.org|author=|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"report4\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fundacioportaventura.org/docs/documentacion/doc_20141113115014.pdf|title=Annual report 2013 Corporate responsibility|date=2014|publisher=fundacioportaventura.org|author=|accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"report5\">{{cite web|url=https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/portaventura-world-production-files/wilson_cms/documents/documents/000/010/744/original/2018_Informe-RC-PA-EN_baixa.pdf|title=Corporate responsibility report 2018|date=2019|publisher=Amazon Web Services|author=|accessdate=August 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|\n! scope=col | 2012\n! scope=col | 2013\n! scope=col | 2014\n! scope=col | 2015\n! scope=col | 2016\n! scope=col | 2017\n! scope=col | 2018\n|-\n! scope=raw | Visits to the parks\n| 3,703,217\n| 3,700,000\n| 3,819,474\n| 3,940,444\n| 3,896,901\n| 4,715,088\n| 4,962,512\n|-\n! scope=raw | Visits to PortAventura Park\n| 3,439,444\n| \n| 3,494,998\n| 3,499,375\n| 3,528,908\n| 3,607,937\n| 3,589,918\n|-\n! scope=raw | Visits to PortAventura Caribe Aquatic Park\n| 263,773\n| \n| 324,476\n| 313,831\n| 367,993\n| 335,351\n| 326,611\n|-\n! scope=raw | Visits to Ferrari Land\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| -\n| 713,421\n| 1,045,983\n|-\n! scope=raw | Visits to Cirque du Soleil\n| -\n| -\n| 100,000\n| 127,238\n| -\n| 58,379\n| -\n|-\n! scope=raw | International visits\n| 35%\n| 38%\n| 36%\n| 33%\n| 33%\n| 33%\n| 36%\n|-\n! scope=raw | Rooms occupied\n| \n| \n| 323,723\n| 334,409\n| 337,219\n| 376,026\n| 390,200\n|-\n! scope=raw | Participants at Convention Centre\n| \n| 44,461\n| 64,536\n| 81,352\n| 72,461\n| 68,782\n| 73,671\n|-\n! scope=raw | Events at Convention Centre\n| \n| \n| 154\n| 184\n| 226\n| 259\n| 201\n|-\n! scope=raw | Total visits <small>(parks, hotels, convention centre)</small>\n| \n| \n| \n| 4,984,092\n| 4,946,389\n| 5,837,509\n| 6,130,308\n|-\n! scope=raw colspan=\"8\"| Balance sheet figures (Thousands of euros)\n|-\n! scope=raw | Non-current assets\n| \n| \n| 913,867\n| 934,196\n| 968,483\n| 997,964\n| 988,362\n|-\n! scope=raw | Current assets\n| \n| \n| 31,939\n| 19,802\n| 27,320\n| 44,740\n| 58,822\n|-\n! scope=raw | Equity and liabilities\n| \n| \n| 945,806\n| 953,998\n| 995,803\n| 1,042,704\n| 1,047,184\n|-\n! scope=raw | Current and non-current liabilities\n| \n| \n| 500,990\n| 492,577\n| 515,062\n| 548,418\n| 543,028\n|-\n! scope=raw colspan=\"8\"| Income statement results (Thousands of euros)\n|-\n! scope=raw | Equivalent turnover\n| 181,200\n| 181,800\n| 194,682\n| 191,160\n| 203,055\n| 234,957\n| 230,349\n|}\n</center>\n\n==PortAventura Park==\n[[File:Entrada a PortAventura Halloween.jpg|thumb|Entrance.]]\n[[File:PortAventura Tutuki Splash.jpg|thumb|The [[Tutuki Splash]] water ride.]]\n{{further|PortAventura Park}}\nThe park features five theme areas based on civilizations (Mediterr\u00e0nia, Far West, M\u00e9xico, China and Polynesia), and one theme area based on [[Sesame Street]]. Mediterr\u00e0nia is the main entrance area of the park.\n;Main rides\n* [[Furius Baco]], an [[Intamin]] [[Accelerator Coaster]] with [[Wing Coaster|winged]] seating, which opened in June 2007. It has a top speed of 83.9&nbsp;mph (135&nbsp;km/h).\n* [[Stampida]], a dueling [[wooden roller coaster]].\n* Tomahawk, a [[wooden roller coaster|junior version]] of Stampida and which runs parallel to it.\n* Silver River Flume, a traditional [[Log flume (ride)|log flume]].\n* Grand Canyon Rapids, a whitewater [[river rapids ride]] along the [[Grand Canyon]].\n* [[Hurakan Condor]], an Intamin [[drop tower]] ride. This ride is one of the tallest in the world at 330&nbsp;ft.\n* El Diablo - Tren de la Mina, an [[Arrow Dynamics]] [[mine train roller coaster]]. The top speed of the coaster is around 60&nbsp;km/h.\n* [[Dragon Khan]], with 8 inversions this formerly held the record as having more inversions than any other [[roller coaster]]. It also held the world record for the tallest vertical loop on any roller-coaster. The ride built by Bolliger & Mabillard was one of the two roller coasters that Port Aventura had when it opened. It consistently ranks among one of the world's best roller coasters in polls.\n* [[Shambhala (roller coaster)|Shambhala]], this B&M [[hypercoaster]] beat three European records as it was the fastest (134&nbsp;km/h) and tallest roller coaster in Europe. It is 76 m tall and had longest drop in Europe at 78 m (2 m underground).\n* Angkor, a large splash battle themed in the [[Angkor]] ruins that opened in 2014.\n* [[Tutuki Splash]], a [[Shoot the Chute]] themed along an erupting volcano.\n* Tami Tami, a roller coaster for children.\n* Street Mission, an interactive Sesame Street dark ride.\n\n==Ferrari Land==\n[[File:Village italien restaurant fl.jpg|thumb|Italian village, Ferrari Land.]]\nInvestIndustrial and [[Ferrari]] signed a deal to build a new area themed to the [[Italy|Italian]] sports car brand in the PortAventura resort covering 75,000 m2, including new rides, a 250-room hotel with restaurants, shops and car racing simulators. Ferrari Land is the resort's second theme park, separate from PortAventura Park. Its entrance is adjacent to PortAventura Park's main entrance. The Mediterranean theme is common to both entrances, as Ferrari Land is inspired by Italy, including recreations of [[Venice]]'s [[Piazza San Marco]] and [[Rome]]'s [[Colosseum]]. The main ride of Ferrari Land is a 112&nbsp;m tall vertical accelerator coaster that surpassed [[Shambhala (roller coaster)|Shambhala]] as the tallest coaster in Europe and is also the fastest coaster in Europe. The park was opened on 7 April 2017, after an investment of more than [[Euro|\u20ac]]100 million.<ref>[http://www.mostreliablecarbrands.com/points-on-the-agenda-ferrari-land-will-open-on-the-7th-of-april-2017]</ref> Ferrari Land opened a kids area in 2018.\n\nFerrari Land is the second amusement centre themed to Ferrari in the world, after [[Ferrari World Abu Dhabi]].<ref name=\"ElPa\u00eds\">{{cite news|title=Port Aventura invertir\u00e1 100 millones en un nuevo parque dedicado a Ferrari|url=http://ccaa.elpais.com/ccaa/2014/03/13/catalunya/1394711022_331793.html|newspaper=[[El Pa\u00eds]]|accessdate=13 March 2014|author=Clara Blanchar}}</ref>\n\n==Some rides and attractions==\n\n===Roller coasters===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#CEDAF2; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black;\"\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:150px;\"|Name\n! style=\"text-align:left;\"|Manufacturer \n! style=\"text-a